**Files modified:**
- `game/src/core/state.js` — Added `randomEvents: null` and `quests: null` fields; reset in initState()
- `game/src/core/events.js` — Added `RANDOM_EVENT` and `QUEST_COMPLETED` event constants
- `game/src/systems/resources.js` — `recalcRates()` now applies `state.randomEvents.activeModifiers` rate multipliers (disaster effects); no import needed, reads state directly
- `game/src/main.js` — Imports and wires initRandomEvents/randomEventTick/initQuests/initQuestPanel; registers randomEventTick as 3rd tick system; initRandomEvents() on New Game reset; save version bumped to 4 (adds randomEvents + quests fields)
- `game/index.html` — Added 🏆 Quests tab button and #panel-quests div
- `game/styles/main.css` — Added styles for .log-entry--raid/windfall/disaster/quest, .quest-header, .quest-list, .quest-card (done/pending variants), .quest-card__* elements, .progress-bar__fill--quest

**Architecture decisions:**
- Disaster modifiers stored in `state.randomEvents.activeModifiers` as `{id, resource, rateMult, expiresAt}` entries; recalcRates() reads them directly — avoids any circular import between randomEvents.js and resources.js
- randomEvents.js imports recalcRates() for immediate effect; recalcRates() reads state.randomEvents without importing the module
- Quest system uses `setQuestPanelRenderer()` callback pattern to let quests.js trigger a UI re-render without importing from questPanel.js
- Quests check on a deferred setTimeout(500ms) after boot so welcome messages appear before any quest rewards that might trigger immediately on load
- Save version 4 is additive; _applySave() uses ?? null defaults so v3 saves load cleanly (just without pre-existing quest/event state)
- Goblin attack has a 40% chance to kill a random unit, making raids have meaningful military consequence; windfalls scale with game tick so late-game rewards stay relevant

